  "body": "With the expected behavior of block parsing per second decreasing in speed as the block height grows, it doesn't seem like it will be long before there are many machines that will never catch up.\r\n\r\nOne of the bragging points of erigon is that \"even a hard drive\" can keep up.\r\n\r\nMaybe if it was synced on an NVMe and copied over to a hard drive.\r\n\r\nBut even on more higher performant hardware, it seems easy to see that block parsing during initial sync will decline to levels that make it take just as long as other approaches to archival node syncing.\r\n\r\nThoughts?\r\n\r\n### Hardware Details\r\n\r\nN/A Its not about me",
